X Series Mrs. America|first=Jordan|last=Crucchiola|work=Vulture|date=October 30, 2018|accessdate=October 23, 2019}}</ref> In November 2019, it was announced the show would premiere on [[Hulu]] instead of FX, as part of \"FX on Hulu\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/fx-produce-programming-hulu-1253252|title=FX to Produce Programming for Hulu|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Natalie|last=Jarvey|first2=Lesley|last2=Goldberg|date=November 7, 2019|accessdate=November 7, 2019}}</ref> In January 2020, it was reported that the series is set to premiere on April 15, 2020.<ref name=\"SeriesPremiereDate\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/fx-sets-premiere-dates-for-fargo-mrs-america-better-things-devs-archer-more-tca-1202825595/|title=FX Sets Premiere Dates For 'Fargo', 'Mrs. America', 'Better Things', 'Devs', 'Archer' & More \u2013 TCA|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|location=Los Angeles, California|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=January 9, 2020|accessdate=January 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nAlongside the series order, [[Cate Blanchett]] was announced to star.<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\"/> In May 2019, [[Uzo Aduba]], [[Rose Byrne]], [[Kayli Carter]], [[Ari Graynor]], [[Melanie Lynskey]], [[James Marsden]], [[Margo Martindale]], [[Sarah Paulson]], [[John Slattery]], [[Jeanne Tripplehorn]] and [[Tracey Ullman]] were added to the series.<ref name=\"cast 1\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/uzo-aduba-james-marsden-sarah-paulson-rose-byrne-cate-blanchett-fx-mrs-america-1202614271/|title=Uzo Aduba, James Marsden, Sarah Paulson, More Join Cate Blanchett in FX's 'Mrs. America'|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|location=Los Angeles, California|first=Anita|last=Bennett|date=May 14, 2019|accessdate=October 23, 2019}}</ref> In June 2019, [[Elizabeth Banks]] was cast to star while Bria Henderson was set to recur.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/elizabeth-banks-cast-mrs-america-fx-limited-series-1202626918/|title=Elizabeth Banks To Co-Star in FX Limited Series 'Mrs. America'|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|location=Los Angeles, California|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=June 4, 2019|accessdate=October 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/p-valley-casts-thomas-q-jones-bria-henderson-joins-mrs-america-1202637912/|title='P-Valley' Casts Thomas Q. Jones; Bria Henderson Joins 'Mrs. America'|last=Petski|first=Denise|date=June 25, 2019|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|location=Los Angeles, California|access-date=January 10, 2020}}</ref> [[Niecy Nash]] was cast in a recurring role in August, with Olivia Scriven cast in October.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/mrs-america-niecy-nash-recur-fx-limited-series-1202669559/|title='Mrs. America': Niecy Nash To Recur in FX Limited Series|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=August 16, 2019|accessdate=October 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/10/mrs-america-olivia-scriven-recur-fx-limited-series-cate-blanchett-1202766260/|title='Mrs. America': Olivia Scriven To Recur in FX Limited Series|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=October 23, 2019|accessdate=October 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nPrincipal photography for the series took place from June 19 to November 1, 2019 in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Current Productions {{!}} IATSE 873 |url=https://www.iatse873.com/current_productions|website=IATSE 873|accessdate=October 23, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191023164713/https://web.archive.org/screenshot/https://www.iatse873.com/current_productions|archivedate=October 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\nThe first three episodes were premiered on [[Hulu]] under '' FX on Hulu'' label on April 15, 2020. In [[India]] the series started streaming on Hulu and FX's corporate sibling [[Disney+ Hotstar]] on April 16, 2020<ref name=\"Firstpost 2020\">{{cite web | title=Mrs. America review: Cate Blanchett and the anti-feminist mystique of FX-Hulu\u2019s ERA-defining drama- Entertainment News, Firstpost | website=Firstpost | date=April 16, 2020 | url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/mrs-america-review-cate-blanchett-and-the-anti-feminist-mystique-of-fx-hulus-era-defining-drama-8266671.html | access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>.\n\n==Reception==\nOn Rotten Tomatoes, the miniseries holds an approval rating of 95% based on 58 reviews, with an average rating of 8.22/10. The website's critical consensus states, \"''Mrs. America'' captures the complicated life and times of Phyllis Schlafly with poise and style to spare, brought to vividlife by a superb ensemble led by another masterful performance from Cate Blanchett.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/mrs_america/s01|title=Mrs. America: Season 1 (2020)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], it has a weighted average score of 87 out of 100 based on 35 reviews, indicating \"universal acclaim\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/mrs-america/season-1|title=Mrs. America: Season 1|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://www.fxnetworks.com/shows/mrs-america}}\n* {{IMDb title|9244556}}\n\n{{Hulu}}\n\n[[Category:2020 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2020s American drama television miniseries]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:FX Networks original programming]]\n[[Category:Hulu original programming]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2020 American drama web television miniseries}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{For|the pageant|Mrs. America}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Mrs. America\n| image                    = Mrs. America (miniseries) Title Card.jpg\n| caption                  =\n| genre                    = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n}}\n| creator                  = [[Dahvi Waller]]\n| writer                   = \n| director                 =\n| starring                 = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Cate Blanchett]]\n* [[Rose Byrne]]\n* [[Uzo Aduba]]\n* [[Elizabeth Banks]]\n* [[Kayli Carter]]\n* [[Ari Graynor]]\n* [[Melanie Lynskey]]\n* [[Margo Martindale]]\n* [[John Slattery]]\n* [[Jeanne Tripplehorn]]\n* [[Tracey Ullman]]\n* [[Sarah Paulson]]\n<!--Starring cast order is according to original credits (the pilot episode). Do NOT rearrange cast order, per MOS:TVCAST. In addition, new starring cast members will be at the bottom of the list.-->\n}}\n| composer                 = [[Kris Bowers]]\n| country                  = United States\n\n| num_seasons              = <!--Only increment as a new season premieres, per the documentation of the template.-->\n| num_episodes             = 3<!--Only increment as a new episode premieres, per the documentation of the template.-->\n| list_episodes            =\n| executive_producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Stacey Sher]]\n* Cate Blanchett\n* [[Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck|Ryan Fleck]]\n* [[Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck|Anna Boden]]\n* Coco Francini\n* Dahvi Waller \n}}\n| producer                 = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Tanya Barfield]]\n* Boo Killebrew\n}}\n| cinematography           = {{Plainlist|\n* Jessica Lee Gagn\u00e9\n* Pepe Avila del Pino\n}}\n| editor                   = {{Plainlist|\n* Robert Komatsu\n* Emily E. Greene\n* Todd Downing\n}}\n| runtime                  = 43\u201348 minutes\n| company                  = {{Plainlist|\n* Shiny Penny Productions\n* Dirty Films\n* Gowanus Projections\n* Federal Engineering\n* [[FX (TV channel)|FXP]]<!--Do not remove, the show while moved to Hulu is still considered an FX Production-->\n}}\n| network                  = [[Hulu]]\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2020|4|15}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|present}}\n| website                  = https://www.fxnetworks.com/shows/mrs-america\n}}\n\n'''''Mrs. America''''' is an American [[Drama (film and television)|drama]] television miniseries about the political movement to pass the [[Equal Rights Amendment]], that premiered on April 15, 2020 on [[Hulu]].<ref name=\"CateB\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/cate-blanchett-star-mrs-america-limited-series-ordered-fx-1202491951/|title=Cate Blanchett To Star In 'Mrs. America' Limited Series Ordered By FX|first1=Nellie|last1=Andreeva|first2=Denise|last2=Petski|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|location=Los Angeles, California|date=October 30, 2018|accessdate=October 23, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"SeriesPremiereDate\"/> [[Cate Blanchett]], [[Rose Byrne]], [[Uzo Aduba]], [[Elizabeth Banks]], [[Margo Martindale]], and [[Sarah Paulson]] star.\n\n==Premise==\n\"Mrs. America tells the true story of the movement to ratify the [[Equal Rights Amendment]], and the unexpected backlash led by a conservative woman named [[Phyllis Schlafly]], played by Blanchett. Through the eyes of the women of that era\u2014both Schlafly and second-wave feminists [[Gloria Steinem]], [[Betty Friedan]], [[Shirley Chisholm]], [[Bella Abzug]] and [[Jill Ruckelshaus]]\u2014the series explores how one of the toughest battlegrounds in the culture wars of the \u201970s helped give rise to the [[Moral Majority]] and forever shifted our political landscape.\"<ref name=\"CateB\"/>\n\n==Cast and characters==\n===Main===\n<!--Main cast order is according to original credits (the pilot episode). Do NOT rearrange cast order, per MOS:TVCAST. In addition, new main cast members will be at the bottom of the list.-->\n* [[Cate Blanchett]] as [[Phyllis Schlafly]]\n* [[Rose Byrne]] as [[Gloria Steinem]]\n* [[Uzo Aduba]] as [[Shirley Chisholm]]\n* [[Elizabeth Banks]] as [[Jill Ruckelshaus]]\n* [[Kayli Carter]] as Pamela\n* [[Ari Graynor]] as [[Brenda Feigen]]\n* [[Melanie Lynskey]] as Rosemary Thomson\n* [[Margo Martindale]] as [[Bella Abzug]]\n* [[John Slattery]] as Fred Schlafly\n* [[Jeanne Tripplehorn]] as Eleanor Schlafly\n* [[Tracey Ullman]] as [[Betty Friedan]]\n* [[Sarah Paulson]] as Alice Macray\n\n===Recurring===\n* [[James Marsden]] as [[Phil Crane]]\n* [[Niecy Nash]] as [[Florynce Kennedy|Flo Kennedy]]\n* Olivia Scriven as Liza Schlafly\n* Bria Henderson as [[Margaret Sloan-Hunter]]\n* [[Jay Ellis]] as [[Franklin A. Thomas|Franklin Thomas]]\n* John Bourgeois as [[George McGovern]]\n* [[Norm Lewis]] as [[Ron Dellums]]\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table |background=#4D5392 |overall= |title= |director= |writer= |airdate= |airdateR=<ref name=\"TFC\">{{cite web |title=Mrs. America \u2013 Listings |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/mrs-america/listings/ |website=[[The Futon Critic]] |accessdate=February 29, 2020}}</ref> |released=y |prodcode= |country=U.S. |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Phyllis\n |DirectedBy      = [[Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck|Anna Boden & Ryan Fleck]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[Dahvi Waller]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|15}}\n |ShortSummary    = <!-- Episode summaries must be expressed in your own words. Do NOT submit content you find from another web site as it is plagiarism and likely a copyright violation, which Wikipedia cannot accept and will be removed or reverted. Superficially modifying copyrighted content or closely paraphrasing it, even if the source is cited, still constitutes a copyright violation. Summaries should be about 100 to 200 words in length, per MOS:TVPLOT, and those substantially less than 100 words are most likely to be scrutinized for possible copyright violation. -->\n |ProdCode        = 101\n |LineColor       = 4D5392\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = Gloria\n |DirectedBy      = Anna Boden & Ryan Fleck\n |WrittenBy       = Dahvi Waller\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|15}}\n |ShortSummary    = <!-- Episode summaries must be expressed in your own words. Do NOT submit content you find from another web site as it is plagiarism and likely a copyright violatio